)@@G@@TEM DESCRIBES THE @DISCS PROCESSOR.  FOR DETAILS ON HOW TO USE    @C@@@@AV
)@@G@@REMOVABLE DISCS, SEE THE NEWS ITEM 'REMDISCS'.  @[@@@@******@[@@@@      AW
)@@G@@@F@@@@NOTE: THE @DISCS PROCESSOR WAS PRIMARILY DESIGNED TO ALLOW THE    AX
)@@G@@@F@@@@      INSTALLATION MANAGEMENT TO OBTAIN DATA CONERNING THE SYSTEM AY
)@@G@@@G@@@@      CONFIGURATION AND STATUS.  IT WILL GIVE ONLY LIMITED INFORMAAZ
)@@G@@TION  @G@@@@      TO THE GENERAL USER, WHO MAY WANT TO KNOW HOW MANY DISBA
)@@G@@C DRIVES    @E@@@@      ARE AVAILABLE OR WHETHER OR NOT HIS PACK IS MOUNBB
)@@G@@TED.  @G@@@@      FEATURES NOT AVAILABLE TO THE GENERAL USER ARE MARKED BC
)@@G@@WITH A *.   @[@@@@      @B@@@@THE CALL IS: @DISCS<,OPTIONS>   <SPEC>    BD
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @D@@@@IF NO OPTIONS OR SPECS ARE GIVEN, EACH REMOVABLE DRIVEBE
)@@G@@@D@@@@WITH A PACK MOUNTED WILL BE LISTED, WITH ITS PACKID,  @C@@@@TRACKSBF
)@@G@@/POSITIONS AVAILABLE, ASSIGN COUNT, ETC.  @[@@@@      @D@@@@* IF A SPEC BG
)@@G@@IS GIVEN, IT MAY TAKE ANY OF THREE FORMS: @E@@@@SS, SS/UU, OR EQUIPMENT-BH
)@@G@@TYPE (E.G. 4, 9/7, OR F17).  IN THIS@E@@@@CASE, ONLY THE INFORMATION FORBI
)@@G@@ THAT UNIT OR EQUIPMENT TYPE  @#@@@@WILL BE LISTED.   @[@@@@      @[@@@@BJ
)@@G@@      @E@@@@OPTIONS:  L - * LONG LISTING, LIST ALL DISC DRIVES, EVEN IF BK
)@@G@@@E@@@@              THEY'RE DOWN OR FIXED.  IF A SPEC IS GIVEN,   @D@@@@BL
)@@G@@              THE L-OPTION IS ASSUMED FOR THAT SPEC.  @G@@@@            BM
)@@G@@  IF THE L-OPTION IS SET, AN ASTERISK MAY APPEAR PRECEDING  @F@@@@      BN
)@@G@@        THE SUBSYSTEM/UNIT NUMBER FOR DISC UNITS, INDICATING@G@@@@      BO
)@@G@@        THAT THIS IS WHERE THE SYSTMM'S REMOVABLE DISC ROTATION   @G@@@@BP
)@@G@@              POINTER IS NOW POINTING.  (THIS DOES NOT NECESSARILY MEAN BQ
)@@G@@@G@@@@              THAT THIS IS THE NEXT DRIVE TO BE SELECTED: IT WILL BR
)@@G@@BE THE@G@@@@              FIRST DRIVE LOOKED AT BY THE SYSTEM WHEN IT ATBS
)@@G@@TEMPTS TO   @B@@@@              MAKE ITS NEXT SELECTION.)   @[@@@@      BT
)@@G@@@E@@@@          F - * PRINT ALL INFO FOR FIXED MASS STORAGE ONLY. @G@@@@BU
)@@G@@              THE PRESENCE OF A SPEC OVERRIDES THIS.  USE OF THE F AND  BV
)@@G@@@G@@@@              L-OPTIONS TOGETHER PRODUCES THE MOST COMPLETE LISTINBW
)@@G@@G     @G@@@@              OF INFORMATION AVAILABLE IN THE FASTRAND AVAILBX
)@@G@@ABILITY     @ @@@@              TABLE (FATBL).  @[@@@@      @F@@@@      BY
)@@G@@    S - PRINTS A SUMMARY OF TRACKS/POSITIONS AVAILABLE ON   @E@@@@      BZ
)@@G@@        EACH EQUIPMENT TYPE (LIKE 'MS' CONSOLE KEYIN).@G@@@@            CA
)@@G@@  * IF A SPEC IS PRESENT, DOES ONLY THAT EQUIPMENT TYPE.    @F@@@@      CB
)@@G@@        NOTE THAT THE SPEC MAY NOT BE A SS OR SS/UU IF THE  @ @@@@      CC
)@@G@@        S-OPTION IS SET.@[@@@@      @D@@@@          P - ACCEPT A PACKID CD
)@@G@@AS SPEC1, AND PRINT INFO@C@@@@              ABOUT IT ONLY, IF IT'S MOUNTCE
)@@G@@ED.   @[@@@@      @F@@@@          A - PRINT NUMBER OF FREE DISC DRIVES, CF
)@@G@@BY EQUIPMENT TYPE.@[@@@@      @E@@@@          M - PRINT INFORMATION GATHCG
)@@G@@ERED FROM THE MCT RATHER@F@@@@              THAN FROM FATBL.  (THE OPTIOCH
)@@G@@NS DESCRIBED SO FAR     @E@@@@              WORK ONLY IF THE M-OPTION ISCI
)@@G@@ NOT SPECIFIED.)  @G@@@@              * IF A SS, SS/UU, OR EQUIPMENT TYPCJ
)@@G@@E IS PRESENT AS SPEC1,  @G@@@@              ONLY INFORMATION ABOUT THAT CK
)@@G@@SPEC WILL BE LISTED.  IF NO   @G@@@@              SPEC IS PRESENT, HOWEVCL
)@@G@@ER, THE ENTIRE SYSTEM CONFIGURATION @G@@@@              WILL BE PRINTED.CM
)@@G@@  UNDER EXEC LEVEL 31 THIS PRINTOUT WILL  @G@@@@              INCLUDE THCN
)@@G@@E SYSTEM ID, LIBLEVEL, SITEID, TIME/DATE OF LAST@G@@@@              REBOCO
)@@G@@OT, MAJOR COMPONENT STATUS, XERR HISTORY, AND OTHER   @F@@@@            CP
)@@G@@  GOODIES.  WITH EARLIER EXECS, A SUBSET OF THE ABOVE @ @@@@            CQ
)@@G@@  IS AVAILABLE.   @[@@@@      @F@@@@          B - ASSUMES M-OPTION, BUT CR
)@@G@@PRINTS ONLY THE INFORMATION   @G@@@@              ABOUT THE LAST REBOOT,CS
)@@G@@ AND THE LAST FEW SYSTEM STOPS.     @[@@@@      @G@@@@       2 OPTIONS HCT
)@@G@@AVE (DIFFERENT) MEANINGS WHEN USED WITH THE M-OPTION: @[@@@@      @F@@@@CU
)@@G@@          S - PRINT ONLY THE MAJOR COMPONENT STATUS INFORMATION.  @G@@@@CV
)@@G@@              IF OMITTED, THE STATUS OF EACH SUBSYSTEM AND UNIT WILL BE CW
)@@G@@@F@@@@              PRINTED AS WELL (ASSUMED FOR THE GENERAL USER).     CX
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @G@@@@          L - * INCLUDE A PRINTOUT OF THE I/O PATHS AVCY
)@@G@@AILABLE TO EACH   @B@@@@              SUBSYSTEM IN THE LISTING.   @[@@@@CZ
)@@G@@      @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @E@@@@THE EQUIPMENT TYPES RECOGNIZED BY @DDA
)@@G@@ISCS ARE AS FOLLOWS:    @[@@@@      @E@@@@    01: 8C        013: 12N    DB
)@@G@@   025: UCS       044: HSP    @E@@@@    02: 6C        014: 16N       030DC

)@@G@@INPUT,OUTPUT,KEYFILE.KEYELT/KEYVER,NREC/LREC    @[@@@@      @^@@@@   ALLMY
)@@G@@OWABLE OPTIONS :  @[@@@@      @G@@@@       N  SUPPRESS ALL PRINTING (INCMZ
)@@G@@L ERROR MESSAGES). OVERRIDES OTHER  @ @@@@           LISTING OPTIONS    NA
)@@G@@@E@@@@       I  SECONDARY TRANSLATION  (NUMBERS BEFORE LETTERS)   @G@@@@NB
)@@G@@       O  ONLY SENSED IF 'I' ALSO SET - FIRST READ ISSUED WILL READ     NC
)@@G@@@G@@@@           A TRANSLATION TABLE OF THE FORM $$$$$...$, WHERE THE $'ND
)@@G@@S     @F@@@@           ARE THE CHARACTERS OF THE FIELDATA CHARACTER SET NE
)@@G@@IN THE@C@@@@           ORDER IN WHICH YOU REQUIRE SORTING.  @F@@@@      NF
)@@G@@     FOR EXAMPLE, THE STANDARD FIELDATA ORDERING, IF READ IN@A@@@@      NG
)@@G@@     IN THIS FORMAT WOULD BE :@[@@@@      @F@@@@ @[]#^ ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQNH
)@@G@@RSTUVWXYZ)-+<=>&$(%:?!,\0123456789';/."_  @[@@@@      @E@@@@         (NONI
)@@G@@TE: THE TRANSLATION TABLE IS INPUT STARTING IN  @E@@@@          COLUMN 2NJ
)@@G@@, TO ALLOW '@' AS THE FIRST CHARACTER.)   @E@@@@           IF THE 'I' OPNK
)@@G@@TION IS SET WITHOUT THE 'O' OPTION  @C@@@@           THE TRANSLATION TABNL
)@@G@@LE HAS THE FORM : @[@@@@      @F@@@@ @[]#^ 0123456789ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSNM
)@@G@@TUVWXYZ)-+<=>&$(%:?!,\';/."_  @[@@@@      @C@@@@       M  DISPLAY THE ENNN
)@@G@@D OF SORT MSG ON CONSOLE@^@@@@       K  LIST THE KEYS @B@@@@       L  PRNO
)@@G@@INT THE RESULTS OF THE SORT   @B@@@@       C  PUNCH THE RESULTS OF THE SNP
)@@G@@ORT   @F@@@@       W  WORD SORT (LREC, KEYSTART AND KEY LENGTH REFER TO NQ
)@@G@@WORDS,@A@@@@           RATHER THAN CHARACTERS.) @F@@@@       R  IF THE ONR
)@@G@@UTPUT FILE IS TAPE, REWIND IT BEFORE WRITING ANY@F@@@@           RECORDSNS
)@@G@@ TO IT (IMPORTANT IF INPUT AND OUTPUT FILE NAMES@G@@@@           REFER TNT
)@@G@@O THE SAME TAPE FILE, AND OVERWRITING IS DESIRED).    @F@@@@           INU
)@@G@@N ANY CASE, TWO HARDWARE EOF MARKS ARE WRITTEN ON THE @G@@@@           ONV
)@@G@@UTPUT TAPE AFTER THE LAST SDF BLOCK (224 WORDS), AND IT     @D@@@@      NW
)@@G@@     IS BACKSPACED OVER ONE OF THE EOF MARKS.   @D@@@@       D  DOUBLE SNX
)@@G@@PACE THE LISTING OF SORTED DATA     @[@@@@      @G@@@@    INPUT IS AN SDNY
)@@G@@F DATAFILE FROM WHICH IMAGES TO BE SORTED ARE TAKEN.  @F@@@@    THE INPUNZ
)@@G@@T FILE MAY BE ONE CREATED BY @DATA, FORTRAN FORMATTED @F@@@@    WRITE, OOA
)@@G@@R IT MAY BE A PRINTFILE (ALTERNATE PRINT OR @BRKPT'D) @F@@@@    AFTER THOB
)@@G@@E KEYS ARE PROCESSED (E.G., WHEN A @EOF IS PROCESSED  @F@@@@    READING OC
)@@G@@KEYS FROM THE RUNSTREAM, OR WHEN THE END OF INPUT     @F@@@@    ELEMENT OD
)@@G@@IS DETECTED IF THE KEYS ARE TAKEN FROM A KEY ELEMENT) @F@@@@    IMAGES TOE
)@@G@@O THE SORT WILL BE READ FROM THE RUNSTREAM.  IN THIS  @F@@@@    WAY, A DOF
)@@G@@ATAFILE CAN BE SORTED, OR A DATAFILE PLUS CARD INPUT  @F@@@@    MAY BE SOG
)@@G@@ORTED TOGETHER, OR CARDS ALONE MAY BE SORTED -- ALL   @F@@@@    WHILE THOH
)@@G@@E OUTPUT IS GOING TO A FILE, BEING PRINTED AND/OR     @C@@@@    PUNCHED,OI
)@@G@@ OR ANY COMBINATION OF THE ABOVE.   @G@@@@    FOR THIS REASON, IT IS NECOJ
)@@G@@ESSARY THAT IF KEY INPUT BE MADE FROM     @G@@@@    THE RUNSTREAM, IT BEOK
)@@G@@ FOLLOWED BY AN EXPLICIT @EOF CARD, AND NOT     @G@@@@    BY ANY OTHER COL
)@@G@@ONTROL CARD.  IF ANY CONTROL CARD OTHER THAN @EOF     @F@@@@    FOLLOWS OM
)@@G@@THE KEY INPUT, THE SORT PROCESSOR WILL ERROR WITH A   @G@@@@    SYMBIONTON
)@@G@@ ERROR CODE 02 (ATTEMPT TO READ AFTER AN ABNORMAL RETURN).  @F@@@@    IFOO
)@@G@@ THE KEY INPUT IS MADE FROM AN ELEMENT, THIS PROBLEM CANNOT @F@@@@    OCOP
)@@G@@CUR, AND ONLY ONE (1) END-OF-FILE RETURN NEED BE EXPLICITLY @B@@@@    MAOQ
)@@G@@DE, AND IT MAY BE ANY CONTROL CARD. @[@@@@      @D@@@@    OUTPUT IS A DAOR
)@@G@@TAFILE TO RECEIVE THE SORTED OUTPUT @[@@@@      @G@@@@    KEYFILE.KEYELTOS
)@@G@@/KEYVER  IS A SYMBOLIC ELEMENT WITH THE KEY INPUT     @[@@@@      @F@@@@OT
)@@G@@    NREC/LREC  =  NUMBER OF RECORDS/LENGTH OF RECORD (LENGTH IS IN@C@@@@OU
)@@G@@       CHARACTERS UNLESS THE W-OPTION IS SET)   @[@@@@      @C@@@@     TOV
)@@G@@HE SIMPLEST FORM OF THE CALL IS  @SORT    @[@@@@      @A@@@@     THE KEYOW
)@@G@@S WILL NOT BE LISTED.   @D@@@@     NO MESSAGE WILL BE DISPLAYED DESCRIBIOX
)@@G@@NG THE SORT.@E@@@@     THE ORDERING OF THE FIELDATA CHARACTER SET IS USEOY
)@@G@@D.    @F@@@@     THE KEYS ARE READ FROM THE RUNSTREAM, FOLLOWED BY A @EOOZ
)@@G@@F.    @E@@@@     DATA TO BE SORTED IS READ FROM THE RUNSTREAM FOLLOWING PA
)@@G@@@B@@@@       THE @EOF TURNING OFF KEY INPUT.    @B@@@@     THE RESULT OFPB
)@@G@@ THE SORT IS PRINTED.   @E@@@@     10000 FOURTEEN WORD RECORDS ARE THE APC
)@@G@@SSUMED SORT INPUT.@F@@@@     NREC/LREC = 10000/84  ASSUMED VALUES IF THIPD
)@@G@@S FIELD IS BLANK. @G@@@@     IF KEY INPUT SPECIFICATION IS MISSING, THE PE

)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@TOC ISXN
)@@G@@ A PROCESSOR FOR LISTING THE TABLES OF CONTENTS OF PROGRAM FILES. @F@@@@XO
)@@G@@ITS OUTPUT IS BETTER SUITED FOR USE FROM DEMAND TERMINALS THAN IS @G@@@@XP
)@@G@@FURPUR'S, AND THE AVAILABLE OPTIONS MAKE IT MORE VERSATILE, AS WELL.    XQ
)@@G@@@F@@@@FULL DOCUMENTATION MAY BE FOUND IN THE LONG VERSION OF THIS ITEM. XR
)@@G@@@[@@@@******@G@@@@THE FOLLOWING DESCRIPTION APPLIES TO TOC 12C AND LATERXS
)@@G@@. THE DIFFERENCES @B@@@@BETWEEN LEVELS 12C AND 12G ARE AS FOLLOWS:@[@@@@XT
)@@G@@      @G@@@@THE P-OPTION IS INCLUDED.  THIS OPTION ASSUMES THE SET <ARS>XU
)@@G@@, AND IS    @F@@@@USED IN CONJUNCTION WITH THE E-OPTION TO LIST THE ELEMXV
)@@G@@ENT TABLE   @A@@@@AS WELL AS THE ENTRY POINT TABLE.   @[@@@@      @G@@@@XW
)@@G@@THE LONG LISTING OF AN ABSOLUTE ELEMENT NOW INCLUDES I-BANK AND D-BANK  XX
)@@G@@@]@@@@LENGTHS.    @[@@@@      @G@@@@THE SHORT LISTING OF A RELOCATABLE EXY
)@@G@@LEMENT INCLUDES ITS SEQUENCE NUMBER,@G@@@@IF THE E-OPTION HAS ALSO BEEN XZ
)@@G@@SPECIFIED. IN ADDITION, THE LONG LISTING  @G@@@@OF RELOCATABLE ELEMENTS YA
)@@G@@INCLUDES THE SECTOR ADDRESSES FOR START OF TEXT @E@@@@AND START OF PREAMYB
)@@G@@BLE, AS WELL AS TEXT AND PREAMBLE LENGTHS.@[@@@@      @G@@@@A BUG CAUSINYC
)@@G@@G SUBSEQUENT @TOC STATEMENTS TO BE IGNORED IF AN EXEC-8     @G@@@@CONTROYD
)@@G@@L STATEMENT OTHER THAN A CALL ON TOC IS SUBMITTED IN ERROR HAS    @F@@@@YE
)@@G@@BEEN FIXED.  TOC WILL ALWAYS RELOAD NOW, WITHOUT THE USE OF @ENDX.@[@@@@YF
)@@G@@      @G@@@@THE 'T' OPTION HAS BEEN IMPLEMENTED.  THIS OPTION TELLS TOC YG
)@@G@@TO LIST     @G@@@@SYMBOLIC ELEMENTS BY SYMBOLIC SUB-TYPE.  THE 'R' AND 'YH
)@@G@@A' OPTIONS ARE    @F@@@@IGNORED IN THE CONTEXT OF RELOCATABLE AND ABSOLUYI
)@@G@@TE, RESPECTIVELY. @G@@@@THE FOLLOWING OPTIONS HAVE MEANING WHEN USED IN YJ
)@@G@@CONJUNCTION WITH THE 'T'@]@@@@OPTION:     @@@@@@@E@@@@ U  LIST UNMARKED YK
)@@G@@SYMBOLIC ELEMENTS AND PROCEDURE ELEMENTS  @A@@@@ E  LIST @ELT PROCESSOR YL
)@@G@@ELEMENTS    @ @@@@ A  LIST ASSEMBLER ELEMENTS   @^@@@@ C  LIST COBOL ELEYM
)@@G@@MENTS @ @@@@ F  LIST FORTRAN ELEMENTS     @^@@@@ M  LIST MAP ELEMENTS   YN
)@@G@@@ @@@@ S  LIST SSG (SKEL) ELEMENTS  @@@@@@@G@@@@IF NONE OF THE ABOVE OPTYO
)@@G@@IONS ARE USED WITH THE 'T' OPTION, ALL SYM-     @E@@@@BOLIC SUBTYPES NOTYP
)@@G@@ LISTED ABOVE ARE LISTED (APL, BAS, ETC.).@@@@@@@G@@@@         TOC IS A YQ
)@@G@@DEMAND ORIENTED PROCESSOR FOR LISTING THE TABLES OF   @G@@@@CONTENTS OF YR
)@@G@@PROGRAM FILES.  TOC PROVIDES, UNDER OPTION LETTER CONTROL,  @F@@@@EITHERYS
)@@G@@ A SHORT OR A LONG LISTING.  THE SHORT LISTING CONTAINS ONLY@G@@@@ELEMENYT
)@@G@@T TYPE, NAME, AND, FOR SYMBOLIC ELEMENTS, THE LATEST CYCLE NUMBER.@G@@@@YU
)@@G@@THE LONG TOC LISTING INCLUDES THE ABOVE, PLUS SEQUENCE NUMBER, CYCLE    YV
)@@G@@@G@@@@WORD FOR SYMBOLIC ELEMENTS, DATE AND TIME OF ELEMENT ENTRY, TEXT LYW
)@@G@@ENGTH @G@@@@AND LOCATION, AND, IF APPLICABLE, FLAGS MARKING THE ELEMENT YX
)@@G@@AS ASCII    @E@@@@SYMBOLIC, THIRD OR QUARTER WORD SENSITIVE, OR IN ERRORYY
)@@G@@.     @[@@@@      @A@@@@         THE PROCESSOR CALL IS:     @[@@@@      YZ
)@@G@@@D@@@@                       @TOC[,OPTIONS] [SPECFIELDS]    @[@@@@      ZA
)@@G@@@F@@@@BRACKETED ITEMS NEED NOT BE PRESENT.  ANY NUMBER OF 'SPECFIELDS', ZB
)@@G@@@A@@@@SEPARATED BY COMMAS, IS PERMISSIBLE.@[@@@@      @G@@@@         AN ZC
)@@G@@EMPTY SPECIFICATION IS TAKEN TO MEAN TPF$.  'SPECFIELD'     @G@@@@IS EITZD
)@@G@@HER A FILE OR ELEMENT NAME.  IF AN ELEMENT NAME IS TYPED, ONLY    @F@@@@ZE
)@@G@@ELEMENTS WITH THAT NAME WILL BE PROCESSED.  LIKEWISE, IF A VERSION@G@@@@ZF
)@@G@@NAME IS SPECIFIED, ONLY ELEMENTS WITH THAT VERSION NAME WILL BE LISTED. ZG
)@@G@@@G@@@@IF A FILE NAME IS SPECIFIED, ALL ELEMENTS WILL BE LISTED (UNDER OPZH
)@@G@@TION  @#@@@@LETTER CONTROL).  @[@@@@      @C@@@@         TOC OPTIONS AREZI
)@@G@@ FROM THE FOLLOWING SET:@[@@@@      @ @@@@     L        LONG LISTING    ZJ
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @B@@@@     X        LIST ONLY DELETED ELEMENTS  @[@@@@      ZK
)@@G@@@B@@@@     A        LIST ONLY ABSOLUTE ELEMENTS @[@@@@      @C@@@@     RZL
)@@G@@        LIST ONLY RELOCATABLE ELEMENTS    @[@@@@      @B@@@@     S      ZM
)@@G@@  LIST ONLY SYMBOLIC ELEMENTS @[@@@@      @C@@@@     E        LIST THE EZN
)@@G@@NTRY POINT TABLE, IF ANY@@@@@@@D@@@@     D        LIST DELETED AND NON-DZO
)@@G@@ELETED ELEMENTS   @@@@@@@F@@@@ANY COMBINATION OF OPTIONS IS PERMISSIBLE.ZP
)@@G@@  IF NONE OF THE SET    @A@@@@<A R S> IS PRESENT, ALL ARE ASSUMED.@[@@@@ZQ
)@@G@@      @]@@@@  EXAMPLES: @[@@@@      @F@@@@         LIST ALL OF THE AVAILZR
)@@G@@ABLE DATA FOR ALL OF THE ABSOLUTE   @ @@@@         ELEMENTS IN 'MYFILE'.ZS
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @A@@@@                   @TOC,LA  MYFILE. @[@@@@      @[@@@@ZT
)@@G@@      @G@@@@         LIST THE NAMES ONLY OF ALL DELETED SYMBOLIC ELEMENTZU
)@@G@@S IN 'PROG'.@[@@@@      @A@@@@                   @TOC,DS  PROG.   @[@@@@ZV
)@@G@@      @[@@@@      @F@@@@         LIST ALL INFORMATION ABOUT ANY ABSOLUTEZW
)@@G@@ OR RELOCATABLE   @F@@@@         ELEMENTS IN TPF$ AND 'PFILE' WITH A VERZX
)@@G@@SION NAME OF 'V1'.@[@@@@      @B@@@@                   @TOC,LRA  /V1,PFIZY
)@@G@@LE./V1@[@@@@      @[@@@@      @#@@@@  OUTPUT FORMATS: @[@@@@      @D@@@@ZZ
)@@G@@SHORT LISTING:     SYMBOLIC:      TYPE  ELT/VERS(C)   @[@@@@      @F@@@@AA
)@@G@@         'TYPE' MAY BE: ASMP, FORP, COBP, SYM, ELT, ASM, COB,     @E@@@@AB
)@@G@@         FOR, ALG, MAP, DOC, SEC, SSG, APL, LSP, BAS, PLS,  @A@@@@      AC
)@@G@@   RUN, ADD, NOR, OR NRL.     @[@@@@      @B@@@@         'C' IS THE LATEAD
)@@G@@ST CYCLE NUMBER.  @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @C@@@@                   RELOCAE
)@@G@@ATABLE:   REL  ELT/VERS @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @C@@@@                  AF
)@@G@@ ABSOLUTE:      ABS  ELT/VERS @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @H@@@@AG
)@@G@@LONG LISTING:      SYMBOLIC:      TYPE ELT/VERS SEQ C DATE-TIME LN LOC FAH
)@@G@@LGS   @[@@@@      @ @@@@         'TYPE' IS AS ABOVE.  @[@@@@      @C@@@@AI
)@@G@@         'SEQ' IS THE ELEMENT'S SEQUENCE NUMBER.@[@@@@      @E@@@@      AJ
)@@G@@   'C' IS THE CYCLE WORD OF THE FORMAT M,L,N WHERE:   @E@@@@            AK
)@@G@@                      M  IS THE CYCLE LIMIT     @F@@@@                  AL
)@@G@@                L  IS THE LATEST CYCLE NUMBER.  @E@@@@                  AM
)@@G@@                N  IS THE CYCLE COUNT.    @[@@@@      @B@@@@         'DAAN
)@@G@@TE-TIME' IS SELF EXPLANATORY. @[@@@@      @D@@@@         'LN' IS THE SECAO
)@@G@@TOR LENGTH OF ELEMENT TEXT.   @[@@@@      @E@@@@         'LOC' IS THE SEAP
)@@G@@CTOR ADDRESS OF THE START OF TEXT.  @[@@@@      @G@@@@         'FLAGS' MAQ
)@@G@@AY BE ANY COMBINATION OF THE SET <A T Q E> WHERE:     @D@@@@            AR
)@@G@@                      A -> ASCII SYMBOLIC @E@@@@                        AS
)@@G@@          T -> THIRD WORD SENSITIVE @F@@@@                              AT
)@@G@@    Q -> QUARTER WORD SENSITIVE     @F@@@@                              AU
)@@G@@    E -> ELEMENT MARKED IN ERROR    @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @H@@@@      AV
)@@G@@             ABSOLUTE:      FORMAT IS THE SAME AS FOR SYMBOLIC, EXCEPT  AW
)@@G@@@G@@@@                                  THAT THE 'C' (CYCLE) FIELD IS ABAX
)@@G@@SENT. @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @G@@@@                   RELOCATABLE:   FOAY
)@@G@@RMAT IS THE SAME AS FOR ABSOLUTE    @G@@@@                              AZ
)@@G@@    ELEMENTS, EXCEPT THAT THE 'LN' FIELD  @F@@@@                        BA
)@@G@@          IS DIVIDED INTO 2 SUB-FIELDS:   @H@@@@                        BB
)@@G@@          PREAMBLE,TEXT.  (THE RELOCATABLE PREAMBLE   @G@@@@            BC
)@@G@@                      FOLLOWS THE LAST SECTOR OF RELOCATABLE@G@@@@      BD
)@@G@@                            TEXT, AND SERVES AS A SOURCE OF DATA  @G@@@@BE
)@@G@@                                  ABOUT THE RELOCATABLE ELEMENT, MAINLY BF
)@@G@@@F@@@@                                  FOR THE USE OF THE COLLECTOR.)  BG
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @#@@@@  SAMPLE OUTPUTS: @[@@@@      BH

)@@G@@L IS A UTILITY LABEL-PRINTING PROCESSOR.  FOR FULL    @C@@@@DETAILS, SEEFT
)@@G@@ THE LONG VERSION OF THIS ITEM.     @[@@@@******@[@@@@      @E@@@@     TFU
)@@G@@O USE THE @LABEL PROCESSOR A CARD DECK OF THE FORM:   @[@@@@      @#@@@@FV
)@@G@@       @LABEL     @^@@@@       PARAMETER CARD   @]@@@@       *    @#@@@@FW
)@@G@@       LABEL 1    @]@@@@       *    @#@@@@       LABEL 2    @]@@@@      FX
)@@G@@ *    @]@@@@       -    @]@@@@       -    @]@@@@       -    @]@@@@      FY
)@@G@@ *    @#@@@@       LABEL N    @^@@@@       @FIN   (OR @EOF) @[@@@@      FZ
)@@G@@@E@@@@ SHOULD BE USED. THE PARAMETER CARD HAS THREE VALUES, EACH  @F@@@@GA
)@@G@@ SEPARATED BY A SPACE, AND TERMINATED BY A '*', ON IT. THEY ARE,  @F@@@@GB
)@@G@@ IN THE ORDER THAT THEY SOULD APPEAR ON THE PARAMETER CARD, AS    @]@@@@GC
)@@G@@ FOLLOWS:   @[@@@@      @E@@@@       NLABELS - NUMBER OF COLUMNS OF LABEGD
)@@G@@LS TO BE PRINTED  @E@@@@       MAXLINE - NUMBER OF LINERS PER LABEL (USUGE
)@@G@@ALLY 5)     @F@@@@       NCOPIES - NUMBER OF COPIES OF EACH LABEL TO BE GF
)@@G@@PRINTED     @[@@@@      @F@@@@     OPTIONS AND SPEC FIELDS, ON THE '@LABGG
)@@G@@EL' CARD, ARE IGNORED.  @F@@@@ EACH LABEL CAN BE A MAXIMUM OF 33 CHARACTGH
)@@G@@ERS WIDE: THERE ARE     @F@@@@ SIX SPACES BETWEEN LABELS HORIZONTALLY, AGI
)@@G@@ND ONE LINE BETWEEN     @F@@@@ LABELS VERTICALLY. MARGINS AND SPECIAL FOGJ
)@@G@@RMS REQUESTS ARE HANDLED@F@@@@ BY THE LABEL PROCESSOR AND THE USER NEED GK
)@@G@@NOT BE CONCERNED ABOUT  @[@@@@ THEM.@[@@@@      @F@@@@     USERS WITH A GL
)@@G@@SINGLE, LARGE, UNCHANGING MAILING LIST SHOULD   @A@@@@ CONSIDER THE FOLLGM
)@@G@@OWING RUNSTREAM:  @[@@@@      @A@@@@       @ASG,T  PRINTAPE,T,PRINTR    GN
)@@G@@@ @@@@       @BRKPT PRINT$/PRINTAPE @#@@@@       @LABEL     @#@@@@      GO
)@@G@@ LABEL-DATA @]@@@@       @FIN @[@@@@      @F@@@@ THIS WILL HAVE THE EFFEGP
)@@G@@CT OF PUTTING THE FORMATTED LABELS ON A   @E@@@@ PRINT TAPE. REPEATED MAGQ

)@@G@@M@^*#@M@^*^@M@^* @M@^*A@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@@CHGN IS A PROCESSOR USED TO CNZ
)@@G@@HANGE CERTAIN PARAMETERS OF CATALOGUED    @F@@@@FILES, SUCH AS OPTIONS, OA
)@@G@@KEYS, ACCOUNT, AND PROJECT.  FOR DETAILS, @A@@@@SEE THE LONG VERSION OF OB
)@@G@@THIS ITEM.  @[@@@@******@[@@@@      @G@@@@    @CHGN IS CAPABLE OF CHANGIOC
)@@G@@NG READ AND WRITE KEYS ON A FILE, AS WELL @G@@@@AS ALTERING PROJECT ID'SOD
)@@G@@ AND ACCOUNT NUMBERS AND CHANGING READ OR WRITE @B@@@@ONLY STATUS, PUBLIOE
)@@G@@C-PRIVATE STATUS,ETC.   @[@@@@      @F@@@@AS A SECURITY PRECAUTION, READOF
)@@G@@ AND WRITE KEYS MAY NOT BE ADDED    @E@@@@TO A FILE WHICH HAS NONE UNLESOG
)@@G@@S THE RUN IS PRIVILEGED OR THE@G@@@@PROJECT I.D. IS THE SAME AS THE ONE OH
)@@G@@UNDER WHICH THE FILE IS CATALOGED   @[@@@@      @^@@@@THE PROCESSOR CALLOI
)@@G@@ IS:  @F@@@@     @CHGN<,OPTS> F[/[R]/[W]].,[F[/[NR]/[NW]].],[N-ACCT],[N-OJ
)@@G@@PROJ] @[@@@@      @D@@@@         WHERE ANY FIELD IN BRACKETS IS OPTIONALOK
)@@G@@, AND @D@@@@         WHERE <OPTS> MAY BE ANY OF THE FOLLOWING:    @[@@@@OL
)@@G@@      @A@@@@         R - SET READ ONLY MODE     @A@@@@         W - SET WOM
)@@G@@RITE ONLY MODE    @ @@@@         P - SET PUBLIC MODE  @ @@@@         V -ON
)@@G@@ SET V OPTION     @ @@@@         G - SET G OPTION     @[@@@@      @G@@@@OO
)@@G@@         NOTE THAT THE ABSENCE OF ANY OF THE ABOVE OPTIONS WILL REMOVE  OP
)@@G@@@ @@@@    THE OPTION IF IT IS SET.  @[@@@@      @B@@@@    THERE ARE FOUROQ
)@@G@@ SPECIFICATION FIELDS:  @[@@@@      @B@@@@    FIELD 1 HAS THE FORM  F[/[OR
)@@G@@R]/[W]].    @A@@@@         WHERE:    F IS THE FILENAME@A@@@@            OS
)@@G@@       R IS THE READ KEY@B@@@@                   W IS THE WRITE KEY     OT
)@@G@@@G@@@@         IT MUST BE NOTED THAT, IF KEYS EXIST, THEY *MUST* BE INCLOU
)@@G@@UDED  @[@@@@      @F@@@@    FIELD 2 HAS THE SAME FORM AS FIELD 1, BUT ISOV
)@@G@@ OPTIONAL, AND    @F@@@@    IS USED FOR CHANGING THE KEYS.  IF IT IS DESOW
)@@G@@IRED TO REMOVE THE@C@@@@    KEYS, JUST THE FILENAME SHOULD BE INCLUDED. OX
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @G@@@@    FIELD 3 IS OPTIONAL, AND, IF PRESENT, ITS CONTENTSOY
)@@G@@ ARE USED FOR THE @^@@@@    NEW ACCOUNT NUMBER. @[@@@@      @G@@@@    FIOZ
)@@G@@ELD 4 IS OPTIONAL, AND, IF PRESENT, ITS CONTENTS ARE USED FOR THE @^@@@@PA
)@@G@@    NEW PROJECT I.D.    @[@@@@      @G@@@@IT SHOULD BE NOTED THAT IF AN PB
)@@G@@ATTEMPT IS MADE TO DO SOMETHING WHICH     @G@@@@REQUIRES THE USER TO BE PC
)@@G@@PRIVILEGED, @CHGN WILL TELL YOU SO.  @CHGN WAS  @G@@@@DESIGNED TO BE SAFPD
)@@G@@E.  THAT IS, IT WILL NOT FREE TPF$ IF A PERIOD IS     @F@@@@FORGOTTEN AFPE
)@@G@@TER THE FILENAME, NOR WILL IT MAKE ANY CHANGES AT ALL @A@@@@IF ANY SINGLPF
)@@G@@E CHANGE IS DISALLOWED. @[@@@@      @G@@@@@CHGN WILL RESTORE THE FILE TOPG

)@@G@@TAT IS A PROCESSOR CAPABLE OF GIVING STATUS OF VARIOUS RUNS, AND  @F@@@@OM
)@@G@@MASS STORAGE STATUS.  IT IS ABLE TO LINK TO @CONFR, ENABLING A    @F@@@@ON
)@@G@@TRANSMISSION AND RECEPTION OF MESSAGES WHILE PROVIDING INFORMATION@D@@@@OO
)@@G@@ABOUT THE SYSTEM.  PLEASE SEE LONG ITEM FOR DETAILS.  @[@@@@******@G@@@@OP
)@@G@@    @STAT IS NYU'S SYSTEM STATUS PROCESSOR.  UNDER OPTION CONTROL, IT   OQ
)@@G@@@G@@@@WILL GIVE THE USER A LIST OF ALL BATCH, DEMAND, BACKLOGGED, OR CLOOR
)@@G@@SED   @F@@@@RUNS, REMOVABLE DISC AVAILABILITY, FASTRAND-FORMATTED MASS SOS
)@@G@@TORAGE@G@@@@AVAILABILITY, OR THE STATUS OF AN INDIVIDUAL RUN IN THE SYSTOT
)@@G@@EM. STAT    @D@@@@CAN ALSO LIST THE PRINT QUEUE FOR A PARTICULAR SITE.  OU
)@@G@@@@@@@@@ @@@@    THE PROCESSOR CALL IS:    @A@@@@         @STAT<,OPTIONS>OV
)@@G@@ <RUNID>    @G@@@@    IF NO OPTIONS ARE PRESENT, 'S' AND 'O' ARE ASSUMEDOW
)@@G@@.  THE FOLLOWING  @D@@@@ARE MEANINGFUL, AND MAY BE USED IN ANY COMBINATIOX
)@@G@@ON:   @@@@@@@C@@@@    A - LIST REMOVABLE DISC DRIVE AVAILABILITY  @ @@@@OY
)@@G@@    B - LIST OPEN BATCH RUNS  @E@@@@        IF THE RUN WAS INTRODUCED TOOZ
)@@G@@ THE SYSTEM VIA A @START@F@@@@        OR A @RSTRT CONTROL CARD, THE RUNIPA
)@@G@@D WILL BE SUFFIXED BY A @D@@@@        SLASH AND AN 'S' OR AN 'R', RESPECPB
)@@G@@TIVELY.     @^@@@@    C - LIST CLOSED RUNS@ @@@@    D - LIST OPEN DEMANDPC
)@@G@@ RUNS @E@@@@    F - LIST FASTRAND-FORMATTED MASS STORAGE AVAILABILITY   PD
)@@G@@@^@@@@    I - IDLE  (2 MIN)   @^@@@@    J - IDLE  (1 MIN)   @^@@@@    K PE
)@@G@@- IDLE  (30 SEC)  @C@@@@    L - LIST CURRENT STATUS OF ALL DISC DRIVES  PF
)@@G@@@#@@@@    N - DO NOTHING@F@@@@    O - LIST ALL OPEN RUNS (COMBINATION OFPG
)@@G@@ 'B' AND 'D' ABOVE)     @G@@@@    P - LIST STATUS OF ALL REMOVABLE DISC PH
)@@G@@DRIVES OR, IF A PACKID IS     @G@@@@        SPECIFIED, LIST ONLY IT'S STPI
)@@G@@ATUS.  IF USED IN COMBINATION WITH  @G@@@@        THE R-OPTION, THE PACKPJ
)@@G@@ID SHOULD BE IN THE VERSION NAME FIELD    @ @@@@    Q - LIST BACKLOGGED PK
)@@G@@RUNS  @G@@@@        THE RUNID MAY BE FOLLOWED BY A SLASH, AND ANY OF SEVPL
)@@G@@ERAL LETTERS@G@@@@          B - RUN HAS BEEN SELECTED FOR OPENING, BUT IPM
)@@G@@NITIAL FACILITIES @D@@@@              STATEMENTS HAVE NOT BEEN PROCESSEDPN
)@@G@@.     @G@@@@          F - RUN IS BEING HELD BECAUSE FACILITIES ARE NOT APO
)@@G@@VAILABLE    @E@@@@          H - RUN IS BEING HELD BY A 'CS H RUNID' KEYIPP
)@@G@@N     @G@@@@          I - THE RUN'S @FIN CARD HAS NOT YET BEEN READ AND PQ
)@@G@@RECOGNIZED. @G@@@@          N - THE NEXT RUN FROM THE SAME INPUT DEVICE PR
)@@G@@IS BEING HELD     @E@@@@              BECAUSE OF AN 'S' OPTION ON ITS @RPS
)@@G@@UN CARD.    @H@@@@          O - INITIAL FACILITIES STATEMENTS HAVE BEEN PT
)@@G@@PROCESSED, BUT RUN      @E@@@@              WAS HELD BECAUSE OF A HIGHERPU
)@@G@@ PRIORITY RUN.    @G@@@@          P - RUN IS BEING HELD BECAUSE THE 'S' PV
)@@G@@OPTION WAS SPECIFIED ON @G@@@@              THE @RUN CARD, AND THE PREVIPW
)@@G@@OUS RUN FROM THE SAME INPUT   @C@@@@              DEVICE HAS NOT YET TERPX
)@@G@@MINATED.    @G@@@@          R - RUN WAS INTRODUCED TO THE SYSTEM VIA A @PY
)@@G@@RSTRT STATEMENT.  @G@@@@          S - RUN WAS INTRODUCED TO THE SYSTEM VPZ
)@@G@@IA A @START STATEMENT.  @G@@@@          T - RUN IS BEING HELD BECAUSE OFQA
)@@G@@ A START-TIME REQUIREMENT.    @ @@@@    R - LIST STATUS OF <RUNID>@B@@@@QB
)@@G@@    S - GIVE A SUMMARY OF SYSTEM STATUS   @G@@@@    T - SAME AS 'O' (FORQC
)@@G@@ COMPATIBILITY WITH OLDER VERSIONS OF STAT)     @E@@@@    U - SUPPRESS PQD
)@@G@@RINTING OF TIMES AND DESCRIPTIVE HEADINGS.@G@@@@    V - LIST ALL QUEUED QE
)@@G@@PRINTFILES AND THE SITE TO WHICH THEY HAVE BEEN @G@@@@        @SYM'MED. QF
)@@G@@ A PARTICULAR SITE MAY BE GIVEN IN THE SAME FORMAT    @F@@@@        AS AQG
)@@G@@ DISC PACK SPECIFICATION.  IF THE V - OPTION IS USED  @F@@@@        WITHQH
)@@G@@ THE P-OPTION, THE SITE NAME SHOULD BE PRECEEDED BY   @D@@@@        A DOQI
)@@G@@LLAR SIGN ($) TO AVOID POSSIBLE CONFUSION.@ @@@@        (SEE P-OPTION, AQJ
)@@G@@BOVE) @G@@@@    W - LIST SITE ID'S FOR ALL DEMAND RUNS, WITH A BREAKDOWNQK
)@@G@@ OF THE     @F@@@@        TERMINAL NAME FOR RUNS THROUGH REAL-TIME, AND QL
)@@G@@LIST DEVICE @A@@@@        ASSOCIATION FOR BATCH RUNS. @G@@@@    X - COMBQM
)@@G@@INATION OF 'R' AND 'I' ABOVE, BUT EXIT WHEN <RUNID> IS NO   @^@@@@      QN
)@@G@@  LONGER FOUND.   @F@@@@    Z - IMMEDIATELY LINK TO CONFR, USING @STAT CQO
)@@G@@ALL OPTIONS ON THE@G@@@@        CONFR CALL.  NO SYSTEM STATUS INFORMATIOQP
)@@G@@N WILL BE DISPLAYED     @B@@@@        UNTIL A @STAT CARD IS ENCOUNTERED.QQ
)@@G@@@@@@@@@F@@@@* IN THE PRESENCE OF ONLY THE A AND/OR R OPTIONS, THE IDLINGQR
)@@G@@ TIME @^@@@@  IS 1/2 OF THAT ABOVE  @@@@@@@G@@@@* IF A DOLLAR SIGN IS INQS
)@@G@@CLUDED IN <RUNID>, IT IS TAKEN AS A TRANSPARENT @G@@@@  CHARACTER.  IF, QT
)@@G@@FOR EXAMPLE, YOU WISHED TO FIND OUT ABOUT RUN 'MYRUN',@G@@@@  BUT AREN'TQU
)@@G@@ SURE THAT THE RUNID HASN'T BEEN MODIFIED BY EXEC-8 (E.G.   @C@@@@  MYRUQV
)@@G@@NA, MYRUNB, ETC.) THE STAT CALL WOULD BE: @^@@@@         @STAT,R MYRUN$ QW
)@@G@@@G@@@@  THIS WOULD FIND ALL RUNIDS WHICH START WITH 'MYRUN', REGARDLESS QX
)@@G@@OF THE@#@@@@  LAST CHARACTER. @@@@@@@F@@@@* AS MANY AS 10 RUNIDS MAY BE QY
)@@G@@INCLUDED OF ONE @STAT CARD:  I.E.   @B@@@@      @STAT,R RUN1,RUN2,RUN3,RQZ
)@@G@@UN4,  (ETC) @ @@@@  LIKEWISE FOR DISC PACK ID'S:@C@@@@      @STAT,P PK20RA
)@@G@@02,PK3003,PK4004,PK9999, (ETC)@F@@@@  IN THE CASE OF THE R, V, AND P OPTRB

)@@G@@*[@@@@*SDFF*@G@@@@    @CONFR IS THE NAME OF N.Y.U.'S DEMAND USERS CONFERGI
)@@G@@ENCE SYSTEM.  IT  @G@@@@ALLOWS TWO OR MORE USERS TO CONVERSE VIA TELETYPGJ
)@@G@@E OR ONE USER TO LEAVE  @F@@@@MESSAGES FOR ANOTHER.  THERE ARE ALSO SOMEGK
)@@G@@ BATCH APPLICATIONS.    @A@@@@PLEASE SEE LONG ITEM FOR DETAILS.   @[@@@@GL
)@@G@@******@[@@@@      @G@@@@    @CONFR'S PRIMARY FUNCTION IS THE TRANSFER OFGM
)@@G@@ INFORMATION FROM ONE   @G@@@@DEMAND TERMINAL TO ANOTHER.  NORMALLY, @COGN
)@@G@@NFR WILL ATTEMPT TO DO SO     @G@@@@INTERNALLY BUT, FAILING THAT, WILL TGO
)@@G@@RANSFER THE DATA TO A PUBLIC MASS   @D@@@@STORAGE FILE WHERE IT MAY BE RGP
)@@G@@EFERENCED AT ANY TIME.  @G@@@@    @CONFR MUST BE ABLE TO IDENTIFY ANY PEGQ
)@@G@@RSON ATTEMPTING TO USE IT.    @G@@@@THIS IS DONE BY USING THE ORIGINAL RGR
)@@G@@UNID FROM THE @RUN CARD.  IT WILL,  @G@@@@HOWEVER, ACCEPT AN ALTERNATE IGS
)@@G@@DENTIFICATION IF DESIRED (SEE R - OPTION  @^@@@@AND P - OPTION, BELOW). GT
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @ @@@@    THE PROCESSOR CALL IS:    @[@@@@      @ @@@@      GU
)@@G@@   @CONFR<,OPTIONS>     @[@@@@      @F@@@@    NO OPTIONS NEED BE PRESENTGV
)@@G@@, BUT THE FOLLOWING ARE RECOGNIZED: @[@@@@      @G@@@@       R - DO NOT GW
)@@G@@USE THE RUNID, BUT ASK FOR AN ALTERNATE IDENTIFICATION@G@@@@       P - DGX
)@@G@@O NOT USE THE RUNID, BUT THE FIRST SIX CHARACTERS FROM THE  @G@@@@      GY
)@@G@@     LATEST @QUAL STATEMENT, OR THE PROJECT ID IF THERE HAS BEEN  @^@@@@GZ
)@@G@@           NO @QUAL.    @[@@@@      @D@@@@       N - DO NOT PRINT QUEUEDHA
)@@G@@ MESSAGES UPON ENTERING @[@@@@      @G@@@@       I - IF THE IDENTIFICATIHB
)@@G@@ON USED IS NOT RECOGNIZED, CREATE A NEW   @D@@@@           ENTRY IN THE HC
)@@G@@TABLE OF ID'S KNOWN TO @CONFR.@C@@@@       M - DO NOT LIST MEMORANDA UPOHD
)@@G@@N ENTERING  @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @G@@@@     @CONFR'S SIGNON LINE WILLHE
)@@G@@ SHOW, AT ITS EXTREME RIGHT, THE NUMBER OF@G@@@@MESSAGES AND MEMORANDA QHF
)@@G@@UEUED FOR YOU.  ANY MEMORANDA WILL BE DISPLAYED,@G@@@@AND THEN NORMAL MEHG
)@@G@@SSAGES WILL BE LISTED.  A MEMO MAY APPEAR MANY TIMES  @F@@@@BUT, ONCE REHH
)@@G@@CEIVED, NORMAL MESSAGES ARE DELETED.  THE LISTING WILL@G@@@@INCLUDE THE HI
)@@G@@ID OF THE ORIGINATOR AS WELL AS THE TIME/DATE OF ORIGIN.    @[@@@@      HJ
)@@G@@@F@@@@    A COMMAND TO CONFR IS ANY IMAGE ENTERED WHICH BEGINS WITH AN  HK
)@@G@@@G@@@@ASTERISK IN COLUMN 1.  ANY OTHER IMAGE IS TREATED AS A MESSAGE.  IHL
)@@G@@N THE @G@@@@FOLLOWING DISCUSSION OF @CONFR COMMANDS, [ID] WILL BE USED THM
)@@G@@O REPRESENT @G@@@@AN IDENTIFICATION OR RUNID.  N, N1, AND N2 WILL REFER HN
)@@G@@TO NUMBERS. IF N, @C@@@@N1, OR N2 APPEARS IN BRACKETS, IT IS OPTIONAL.  HO
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @#@@@@    COMMANDS:     @[@@@@      @G@@@@         *TO   [LIHP
)@@G@@ST]   THE *TO COMMAND INDICATES TO @CONFR THAT ALL    @G@@@@            HQ
)@@G@@            FOLLOWING IMAGES ARE TO BE SENT TO THE ID'S     @G@@@@      HR
)@@G@@                  IN [LIST].  IF [LIST] IS ABSENT, THE CURRENT    @G@@@@HS
)@@G@@                        LIST WILL BE DISPLAYED.  [LIST] MAY CONSIST OF  HT
)@@G@@@G@@@@                        ONE TO FIFTEEN ID'S WHICH ARE KNOWN TO @COHU
)@@G@@NFR.  @G@@@@                        [LIST] MAY BE PRECEEDED BY A PLUS ORHV
)@@G@@ A MINUS, IN@G@@@@                        WHICH CASE THE ID'S IN [LIST] HW
)@@G@@WILL BE ADDED TO  @G@@@@                        OR REMOVED FROM THE CURRHX
)@@G@@ENT LIST, RESPECTIVELY. @G@@@@                        THE LIST MAY BE CLHY
)@@G@@EARED BY PLACING AN ASTERISK  @C@@@@                        IN PLACE OF HZ
)@@G@@[LIST].     @[@@@@      @F@@@@         *MEMO          THE GENERAL FORM OIA
)@@G@@F THE MEMO COMMAND IS:  @D@@@@                           *MEMO [ID][*MM/IB
)@@G@@DD],[MSG]   @F@@@@                        THE *MEMO COMMAND SENDS A SPECIC
)@@G@@IAL TYPE OF @G@@@@                        MESSAGE TO [ID].  THE MESSAGE ID
)@@G@@WILL BE DISPLAYED @G@@@@                        EVERY TIME THE RECIEVER IE
)@@G@@ENTERS @CONFR UNTIL HE  @G@@@@                        USES THE *CM COMMAIF
)@@G@@ND (BELOW) TO REMOVE IT, OR   @G@@@@                        THE EXPIRATIIG
)@@G@@ON DATE HAS PASSED.  IF THE DATE IS @G@@@@                        OMITTEIH
)@@G@@D, THE MEMO WILL ALWAYS BE DISPLAYED UNTIL@G@@@@                        II
)@@G@@THE *CM COMMAND IS USED.  IF [ID] IS OMITTED,   @G@@@@                  IJ
)@@G@@      THE RULES GOVERNING UNIDENTIFIED MESSAGES APPLY.@D@@@@            IK
)@@G@@            (SEE *TO AND *PARTY ABOVE)    @[@@@@      @G@@@@         *CMIL
)@@G@@            THE *CM COMMAND COMPLETELY CLEARS ALL MEMORANDA.@[@@@@      IM
)@@G@@@F@@@@         *AC            LIST ALL USERS CURRENTLY ACTIVE IN @CONFR IN
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @G@@@@         *LAC  [ID]     LIST THE TIME/DATE THAT [ID] WIO
)@@G@@AS LAST ACTIVE    @G@@@@                        IN @CONFR.  IF [ID] IS AIP
)@@G@@BSENT, DO SO FOR ALL    @G@@@@                        KNOWN ID'S.   *LACIQ
)@@G@@ WILL ACCEPT SEVERAL ID'S, AS:@C@@@@                          *LAC  ID1,IR
)@@G@@ID2,...,IDN @G@@@@                        TO LIST ALL ID'S THAT HAVE BEEIS
)@@G@@N ACTIVE SINCE A  @F@@@@                        CERTAIN DATE,  THE FORM IT
)@@G@@IS:  *LAC *MM/DD. @F@@@@                        IF MM/DD IS LEFT OFF, TOIU
)@@G@@DAY'S DATE WILL BE@F@@@@                        ASSUMED, BUT THE ASTERISIV
)@@G@@K MUST BE PRESENT.@[@@@@      @C@@@@         *EXIT          TERMINATE THIW
)@@G@@E PROGRAM   @[@@@@      @G@@@@         *RCV  [ID]     THE *RCV COMMAND CIX
)@@G@@ONTROLS MESSAGE RECEPTION.    @F@@@@                        IF [ID] IS PIY
)@@G@@RESENT AND KNOWN TO CONFR, THE@G@@@@                        MESSAGES QUEIZ
)@@G@@UED FOR YOU WILL BE INSPECTED AND   @F@@@@                        ONLY TJA
)@@G@@HE ONES FROM [ID] WILL BE DISPLAYED.@G@@@@                        IF [IDJB
)@@G@@] IS NOT KNOWN TO CONFR, RECEPTION IS     @G@@@@                        JC
)@@G@@TURNED OFF COMPLETELY.  IF [ID] IS ABSENT, ALL  @G@@@@                  JD
)@@G@@      MESSAGES, REGARDLESS OF ORIGIN, WILL BE LISTED. @[@@@@      @G@@@@JE
)@@G@@         *KEY  [W]      THIS IS FOR THOSE WHO ARE SECURITY CONSCIOUS.   JF
)@@G@@@G@@@@                        [W] IS A LEFT-ADJUSTED SPACE-FILLED WORD WJG
)@@G@@HICH  @G@@@@                        MUST BE SUPPLIED BY YOU ON ALL SUBSEJH
)@@G@@QENT CALLS  @G@@@@                        TO @CONFR.  IT IS STRONGLY RECJI
)@@G@@OMMENDED THAT THE @G@@@@                        KEY NOT BEGIN WITH A '@'JJ
)@@G@@.  TO REMOVE AN EXISTING@G@@@@                        KEY, THE *KEY COMMJK
)@@G@@AND SHOULD BE USED WITH [W]   @F@@@@                        BLANK.  [W] JL
)@@G@@MAY BE ANY COMBINATION OF 1-6 @D@@@@                        CHARACTERS (JM
)@@G@@EXCLUDING BLANKS).@[@@@@      @F@@@@         *LC   [*]      LOCATE ALL MJN
)@@G@@ESSAGES SENT BY YOU, GIVING   @G@@@@                        DESTINATION JO
)@@G@@AND A COUNT OF THE MESSAGES FOR     @G@@@@                        THAT DJP
)@@G@@ESTINATION.  IF THE ASTERISK IS PRESENT,  @D@@@@                        JQ
)@@G@@THE MESSAGES WILL BE LISTED.  @[@@@@      @F@@@@         *EDIT [ID][*]  JR
)@@G@@THIS COMMAND IS USED TO INITIATE A MESSAGE@G@@@@                        JS
)@@G@@EDITOR.  THE EDITOR'S COMMANDS ARE UNIQUE TO    @G@@@@                  JT
)@@G@@      ITSELF, AND ARE SIMILAR TO COMMANDS FOUND IN    @G@@@@            JU
)@@G@@            NORMAL TEXT EDITORS, SUCH AS @EDQ AND @EDN,     @F@@@@      JV
)@@G@@                  ALTHOUGH THE COMMAND SET IS VERY LIMITED. @D@@@@      JW
)@@G@@                  THE COMMANDS ARE AS FOLLOWS:  @C@@@@                  JX
)@@G@@         T - GO TO THE TOP    @C@@@@                           G [N] - GJY
)@@G@@O TO LINE N @G@@@@                           N [N] - GO TO LINE N PAST TJZ
)@@G@@HE CURRENT LINE   @F@@@@                           U [N] - GO UP N LINESKA
)@@G@@ FROM THE CURRENT @C@@@@                           P [N] - PRINT N LINESKB
)@@G@@@D@@@@                           D [N] - DELETE N LINES     @G@@@@      KC
)@@G@@                     I [MSG] - INSERT [MSG] FOLLOWING THE CURRENT @B@@@@KD
)@@G@@                                     LINE.@G@@@@                        KE
)@@G@@   R [MSG] - REPLACE THE CURRENT MESSAGE WITH   @C@@@@                  KF
)@@G@@                   [MSG].     @F@@@@                        * CURRENTLY KG
)@@G@@THERE IS NO CHANGE COMMAND.   @F@@@@                        [ID] ON THE KH
)@@G@@*EDIT COMMAND IS OPTIONAL.  IF@G@@@@                        ABSENT, THE KI
)@@G@@IDENT FROM THE LATEST *TO COMMAND   @G@@@@                        IS ASSKJ
)@@G@@UMED.  THE OPTIONAL ASTERISK, IF PRESENT, @G@@@@                        KK
)@@G@@INDICATES THAT MEMORANDA, RATHER THAN NORMAL    @G@@@@                  KL
)@@G@@      MESSAGES ARE TO BE EDITED.  PLEASE NOTE THAT    @G@@@@            KM
)@@G@@            THE EDITOR REQUIRES A LARGE AMOUNT OF I/O, AND  @G@@@@      KN
)@@G@@                  SHOULD THEREFORE NOT BE USED INDISCRIMINATELY.  @F@@@@KO
)@@G@@                        EDIT MODE MUST BE TERMINATED BEFORE NORMAL@G@@@@KP
)@@G@@                        CONFERENCE MESSAGES MAY BE SENT OR RECEIVED.    KQ
)@@G@@@G@@@@                        THIS IS ACCOMPLISHED BY USING THE *END COMKR
)@@G@@MAND, @G@@@@                        OR ANY OTHER @CONFR COMMAND, SUCH ASKS
)@@G@@ *AC, *TO,  @ @@@@                        ETC.  @G@@@@         *ND      KT
)@@G@@      THE *ND COMMAND CAUSES ALL FURTHER MESSAGES TO  @E@@@@            KU
)@@G@@            BE TAGGED WITH A NEW DATE/TIME.     @G@@@@         *TD      KV
)@@G@@      THE *TD COMMAND CAUSES THE CONFERENCE SYSTEM    @G@@@@            KW
)@@G@@            SIGN-ON LINE TO BE REPRINTED, WITH THE CURRENT  @B@@@@      KX
)@@G@@                  TIME AND DATE.    @[@@@@      @[@@@@      @[@@@@NOTES:KY
)@@G@@@ @@@@    1.   IDENTIFIED MESSAGES  @[@@@@      @G@@@@         A MESSAGEKZ
)@@G@@ MAY BE SENT TO A PARTICULAR IDENT REGARDLESS OF A    @B@@@@         *TOLA
)@@G@@ IN EFFECT.   THE FORM IS:    @ @@@@              *[ID]:[MSG]     @E@@@@LB

)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@HAT NUMBER MINUS 1 LINES.     @F@@@@          IFBD
)@@G@@ EITHER OF THE FIRST TWO NUMBERS ARE OMITTED OR 0,    @D@@@@          THBE
)@@G@@E RESPECTIVE END OF THE LINE IS UNCHANGED.@[@@@@      @E@@@@ D        DEBF
)@@G@@LETE THE NUMBER OF LINES SPECIFIED, STARTING    @D@@@@          WITH THEBG
)@@G@@ CURRENT LINE.  IF A SECOND FIELD IS@E@@@@          GIVEN, DELETE THE N1BH
)@@G@@TH LINE THROUGH THE N2TH LINE,@B@@@@          RELATIVE TO THE CURRENT LIBI
)@@G@@NE.   @@@@@@@E@@@@ C        CHANGE - THE FORMAT OF THE CHANGE COMMAND ISBJ
)@@G@@:     @[@@@@      @ @@@@          C /STRING1/STRING2/ @[@@@@      @G@@@@BK
)@@G@@          THE '/' IS A GENERAL DELIMITER, AND MAY BE REPLACED BY ANY    BL
)@@G@@@E@@@@          CHARACTER NOT APPEARING IN 'STRING1' OR 'STRING2'.@F@@@@BM
)@@G@@          IF THE LETTER 'G' FOLLOWS THE THIRD DELIMITER, ALL OC-  @F@@@@BN
)@@G@@          CURRANCES OF 'STRING1' IN THE CURRENT LINE ARE CHANGED  @F@@@@BO
)@@G@@          'STRING2'.  IF A NUMBER FOLLOWS THE THIRD DELIMITER, THE@F@@@@BP
)@@G@@          CHANGE COMMAND CONTINUES FOR THAT NUMBER MINUS 1 LINES. @E@@@@BQ
)@@G@@          IN ADDITION, 'G' MAY FOLLOW A NUMBER SO SPECIFIED.@F@@@@      BR
)@@G@@    IF THE LETTER 'A' FOLLOWS THE THIRD DELIMITER, EDN PER- @F@@@@      BS
)@@G@@    FORMS A TOP, THEN CHANGES ALL OCCURRANCES OF 'STRING1'  @B@@@@      BT
)@@G@@    TO 'STRING2' IN THE ENTIRE TEXT.@[@@@@      @@@@@@@G@@@@          ADBU
)@@G@@DITIONAL INFORMATION ON THE 'I', 'IB', 'R', 'A' AND 'S'     @G@@@@      BV
)@@G@@    COMMANDS:  THE FORMAT 'COMMAND+NUMBER' CAUSES THE NEW CHAR-   @E@@@@BW
)@@G@@          ACTERS (LINE) TO BE STORED STARTING AT THE COLUMN @G@@@@      BX
)@@G@@    NUMBER SPECIFIED.  THUS, 'I+5 ABC' CAUSES THE STRING 'ABC' TO @F@@@@BY
)@@G@@          BE INSERTED AS A NEW LINE OF TEXT, STARTING AT COLUMN 5.@@@@@@BZ
)@@G@@@@@@@@@[@@@@      @^@@@@  5.      BLOCK EDITING @[@@@@      @E@@@@ SPL  CA
)@@G@@    THE NUMBER OF LINES SPECIFIED ARE COPIED INTO AN  @F@@@@          INCB
)@@G@@TERNAL FILE.  THEY MAY BE ADDED LATER.  THE TEXT IS   @^@@@@          UNCC
)@@G@@CHANGED.    @[@@@@      @E@@@@ SPD      THE NUMBER OF LINES SPECIFIED ARCD
)@@G@@E COPIED AS IN    @F@@@@          THE CASE OF 'SPL', HOWEVER, THEY ARE ACE
)@@G@@LSO DELETED FROM  @^@@@@          THE TEXT.     @@@@@@@E@@@@ SPL!     A CF
)@@G@@TOP IS PERFORMED, AND THE ENTIRE TEXT IS COPIED.@[@@@@      @G@@@@ SAVE CG
)@@G@@    SAME AS 'SPL!', EXCEPT THE EDITOR RETURNS TO THE LINE THAT    @F@@@@CH
)@@G@@          THAT WAS BEING EDITED WHEN THE 'SAVE' WAS EXECUTED.     @@@@@@CI
)@@G@@@G@@@@ AUTO     SPECIFIES THE NUMBER OF CORRECTIONS TO BE APPLIED BEFORECJ
)@@G@@ AN   @G@@@@          AUTOMATIC SAVE OF THE EDITED TEXT IS PERFORMED, ASCK
)@@G@@ IF A 'SAVE'@G@@@@          COMMAND HAD BEEN EXECUTED.  IF THE NUMBER SPCL
)@@G@@ECIFIED IS LESS   @G@@@@          THAN OR EQUAL TO ZERO, AUTO MODE IS TUCM
)@@G@@RNED OFF.  IT IS RECOM- @G@@@@          MENDED THAT BLOCK EDITING VIA 'SCN
)@@G@@PL' TYPE COMMANDS NOT BE USED @G@@@@          IF IN AUTO MODE, AS THE SACO
)@@G@@ME FILE ('SPLIT$') IS USED FOR BOTH.@G@@@@          IF IN INPUT MODE, ANCP
)@@G@@ AUTO SAVE IS DONE AFTER THE GIVEN NUMBER @G@@@@          OF LINES HAS BCQ
)@@G@@EEN INPUT.  AUTO MODE IS SUSPENDED IF IN AN @ADD@#@@@@          FILE.   CR
)@@G@@@@@@@@@F@@@@ ADD      THE LAST BLOCK SPLIT FROM THE TEXT IS INSERTED INTCS
)@@G@@O     @G@@@@          THE TEXT FOLLOWING THE CURRENT LINE.  THE NUMBER OCT
)@@G@@F LINES     @F@@@@          ADDED IS DISPLAYED.  THE 'A' OPTION ON THE ECU
)@@G@@DN CALL CARD@G@@@@          CAUSES AN 'ADD' COMMAND TO BE FORCED DURING CV
)@@G@@INITIALIZATION.   @F@@@@          THUS, IF DURING EDITING AN 'SAVE' IS ECW
)@@G@@XECUTED SAVING    @G@@@@          THE EDITED TEXT AND THE SYSTEM CRASHESCX
)@@G@@, THE EDITED TEXT MAY   @G@@@@          BE RESTORED WITH ONLY THOSE CHANCY
)@@G@@GES MADE AFTER THE 'SAVE'     @ @@@@          HAVING BEEN LOST.   @]@@@@CZ
)@@G@@            @@@@@@@@@@@@@A@@@@  6.      SAVING INDIVIDUAL LINES   @[@@@@DA
)@@G@@      @E@@@@ HL       SAVES THE CURRENT LINE IN AN INTERNAL EDN ARRAY.  DB
)@@G@@@F@@@@          THE LINE MAY BE REENTERED LATER ANYWHERE IN THE TEXT.   DC
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @G@@@@ HD       SAME AS 'HL', BUT THE LINE IS ALSO DELETED FDD
)@@G@@ROM THE TEXT.     @[@@@@      @E@@@@ EH       ENTERS A LINE INTO THE HOLDE
)@@G@@D AREA FROM THE COMMAND,@A@@@@          RATHER THAN FROM THE TEXT.@@@@@@DF
)@@G@@@D@@@@ PH       DISPLAYS ON THE TERMINAL THE LAST LINE HELD.@[@@@@      DG
)@@G@@@E@@@@ IH       INSERTS THE LAST LINE HELD INTO THE TEXT FOLLOWING@ @@@@DH
)@@G@@          THE CURRENT LINE.   @[@@@@      @D@@@@ IHB      INSERTS A HELDDI
)@@G@@ LINE BEFORE THE CURRENT LINE.@[@@@@      @D@@@@ RH       REPLACES THE CDJ
)@@G@@URRENT LINE WITH A HELD LINE. @[@@@@      @E@@@@ AH       PERFORMS AN 'ADK
)@@G@@' OPERATION ON THE CURRENT LINE WITH@ @@@@          THE LAST LINE HELD. DL
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @E@@@@ CH       CONCATENATES THE CURRENT LINE WITH THE LINE DM
)@@G@@IN THE@^@@@@          HOLD AREA.    @[@@@@      @G@@@@          IF A NUMDN
)@@G@@BER APPEARS ON THE 'IH', 'IHB', 'RH', OR 'AH COMMANDS,@G@@@@          THDO
)@@G@@E REQUESTED OPERATION WILL START AT THE COLUMN SO SPECIFIED.@[@@@@      DP
)@@G@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@^@@@@  7.      TEXT SEARCHING@[@@@@      @G@@@@          THDQ
)@@G@@E COMMANDS 'L' AND 'F' ARE THE BASIC TEXT SEARCHING COM-    @G@@@@      DR
)@@G@@    ANDS. EACH SCANS ALL LINES FOLLOWING THE CURRENT LINE FOR A   @G@@@@DS
)@@G@@          MATCH ON THE STRING APPEARING ON THE COMMAND LINE.  THE DIF-  DT
)@@G@@@G@@@@          FERENCE BETWEEN THE TWO IS THAT 'L' WILL FIND THE SUBJECDU
)@@G@@T     @G@@@@          STRING ANYWHERE IN THE TEXT, WHILE 'F' MUST MATCH DV
)@@G@@STARTING AT @G@@@@          THE COLUMN NUMBER ON THE COMMAND RELATIVE TODW
)@@G@@ THE END OF THE   @ @@@@          OPERATION FIELD.    @[@@@@      @#@@@@DX
)@@G@@          EXAMPLE:@[@@@@      @#@@@@          L 1234  @[@@@@      @G@@@@DY
)@@G@@          WILL FIND THE STRING '1234' ANYWHERE IN THE TEXT.  ON THE     DZ
)@@G@@@^@@@@          OTHER HAND:   @[@@@@      @#@@@@          F 1234  @[@@@@EA
)@@G@@      @G@@@@          WILL FIND '1234' ONLY IF IT STARTS IN COLUMN 1.  FEB
)@@G@@URTHERMORE, @[@@@@      @#@@@@          F   1234@[@@@@      @G@@@@      EC
)@@G@@    WILL FIND '1234' ONLY AT COLUMN 3.  THE FORMAT 'F+NUMBER' IS  @G@@@@ED
)@@G@@          LEGAL, AND WILL FIND THE STRING STARTING AT THE COLUMN NUMBER EE
)@@G@@@F@@@@          GIVEN.  THIS DISTINCTION HOLDS TRUE FOR ALL SEARCHES.   EF
)@@G@@@[@@@@      @F@@@@          IF THE SEARCH COMMAND OPERATION FIELD IS TEREG
)@@G@@MINATED WITH@F@@@@          A PERIOD, OR THE OPERATION AND OPTIONAL NUMEEH
)@@G@@RIC FIELD   @G@@@@          FOR THE 'F' TYPE COMMANDS, THE SEARCH WILL SEI
)@@G@@UCCEED AT THE     @E@@@@          FIRST LINE NOT CONTAINING THE SUBJECT EJ
)@@G@@STRING.     @@@@@@@#@@@@          EXAMPLE:@@@@@@@#@@@@          F 1234  EK
)@@G@@@@@@@@@F@@@@          AS ABOVE, FINDS THE FIRST OCCURANCE OF '1234' AT CEL
)@@G@@OLUMN @^@@@@          ONE, WHILE:   @@@@@@@#@@@@          F.1234  @@@@@@EM
)@@G@@@G@@@@          FINDS THE FIRST LINE NOT CONTAINING '1234' STARTING AT CEN
)@@G@@OLUMN @G@@@@          ONE.  TO FIND THE FIRST BLANK LINE FOLLOWING THE CEO
)@@G@@URRENT LINE,@@@@@@@#@@@@          F.@     @@@@@@@G@@@@          WILL WOREP
)@@G@@K, AS LONG AS '@' RETAINS ITS INITIAL PROPERTY AS THE @E@@@@          TREQ
)@@G@@ANSPARENT CHARACTER FOR 'F' AND 'L' COMMANDS.   @G@@@@          LIKEWISEER
)@@G@@, TO FIND THE FIRST NON-OCCURANCE OF A BLANK IN COL-  @F@@@@          UMES
)@@G@@N ONE (AN ASSEMBLY LANGUAGE LABEL, FOR INSTANCE),     @@@@@@@#@@@@      ET
)@@G@@    F. @    @@@@@@@^@@@@          WILL WORK.    @@@@@@@F@@@@          **EU
)@@G@@ NOTE **  WHEN THE OPERATION FIELD IS TERMINATED WITH @G@@@@          A EV
)@@G@@PERIOD, THE PERIOD IS IN PLACE OF THE SPACE USUALLY USED    @G@@@@      EW
)@@G@@    TO TERMINATE THE COMMAND FIELD.  THUS 'F.1234' AND F. 1234'   @G@@@@EX
)@@G@@          ARE NOT EQUIVALENT--THE FIRST FINDS THE FIRST NON-OCCURANCE OFEY
)@@G@@@H@@@@          '1234' AT COLUMN ONE, AND THE SECOND FINDS THE FIRST NONEZ
)@@G@@-OCCUR-     @G@@@@          ANCE OF '1234' AT COLUMN TWO, WITH A BLANK IFA
)@@G@@N COLUMN ONE.     @@@@@@@F@@@@ LP       LOCATE THE STRING GIVEN, PRINTINFB
